{"name":"Hive","type":"starshipExpansionBay","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"cost":2,"costMultipliedBySize":false,"pcu":2,"isPowered":true,"description":{"chat":"","gmnotes":"","short":"","value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Name PCU Cost (In BP)<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Hive 2 2<br>Rift 10 3<br>Shrine, Basic 1 1<br>Shrine, Advanced 3 2<br>Shrine, Opulent 10 5</span></p><h3><span class=\"fontstyle3\">H</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"font-size:9pt;\">ive</span></h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">This very specific science lab is filled with dense plant life and equally copious insects of all varieties. Its generous tools and herbal supplies grant a +2 circumstance bonus to Life Science checks. The insects learn to tolerate the presence of the crew, but if unleashed through the ship, will attack any being they recognize as living but unfamiliar. The hive can be used to create a vermin swarm of a CR equal to three or less once a day. The swarm will disperse and return to the hive after an hour. Multiple hives can be purchased, increasing the CR of the summoned swarm by 3 for each additional hive. The swarm will not leave the ship. Unleashing the swarm requires an action.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p>","unidentified":""},"source":"","type":"","modifiers":[],"damage":{"parts":[]},"critical":{"parts":[]},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"sfrpg","systemVersion":"0.22.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672510147667,"modifiedTime":1673333903583,"lastModifiedBy":"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY"},"_id":"9ZVITicRmeT90Fch","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY":3}}
{"name":"Rift","type":"starshipExpansionBay","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"cost":3,"costMultipliedBySize":false,"pcu":10,"isPowered":true,"description":{"chat":"","gmnotes":"","short":"","value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Name PCU Cost (In BP)<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Hive 2 2<br>Rift 10 3<br>Shrine, Basic 1 1<br>Shrine, Advanced 3 2<br>Shrine, Opulent 10 5</span></p><h3><span class=\"fontstyle0\">R</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-size:9pt;\">ift</span></h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle1\">This energy-intensive room is designed to breach into one of the elemental planes and allow it to pour safely, at least for the rest of the ship, into the room. Being in the room exposes one to the full effects of being on that plane, including any elemental hazards, breathing difficulties, or other problems. Such spaces can be helpful if one deals heavily in the elements, as the elementally charged people of Everglow are often found doing. Attempts to call or summon things native of the aligned elemental plane are done so more easily, Giving a +2 circumstance bonus to rolls involving calling, negotiating, or controlling such creatures. The element of a rift can only be changed with 1d4 day’s effort and a DC 17 Engineering and DC 20 Mysticism check. Failing either by 5 or more causes the rift to go unstable, wrecking it and inflicting 3d10 damage on the ship.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p>","unidentified":""},"source":"","type":"","modifiers":[],"damage":{"parts":[]},"critical":{"parts":[]},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"sfrpg","systemVersion":"0.22.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672510147667,"modifiedTime":1673333903583,"lastModifiedBy":"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY"},"_id":"NQZJX2jerM0vaPiy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY":3}}
{"name":"Shrine, Advanced","type":"starshipExpansionBay","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"cost":2,"costMultipliedBySize":false,"pcu":3,"isPowered":true,"description":{"chat":"","gmnotes":"","short":"","value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Name PCU Cost (In BP)<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Hive 2 2<br>Rift 10 3<br>Shrine, Basic 1 1<br>Shrine, Advanced 3 2<br>Shrine, Opulent 10 5</span></p><h3><span class=\"fontstyle0\">S</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-size:9pt;\">hrine, Advanced</span></h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Advanced models can be made for entire pantheons to be shared with different related faiths, or to provide a comfortable space for a specific god with some measure of reverence and glory. They are considered blessed or consecrated for sake of effects that react to such things, but provides no mechanical benefit.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p>","unidentified":""},"source":"","type":"","modifiers":[],"damage":{"parts":[]},"critical":{"parts":[]},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"sfrpg","systemVersion":"0.22.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672510147667,"modifiedTime":1673333903583,"lastModifiedBy":"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY"},"_id":"d6EnH0PAD4w3knYH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY":3}}
{"name":"Shrine, Basic","type":"starshipExpansionBay","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"cost":1,"costMultipliedBySize":false,"pcu":1,"isPowered":true,"description":{"chat":"","gmnotes":"","short":"","value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Name PCU Cost (In BP)<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Hive 2 2<br>Rift 10 3<br>Shrine, Basic 1 1<br>Shrine, Advanced 3 2<br>Shrine, Opulent 10 5</span></p><h3><span class=\"fontstyle0\">S</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-size:9pt;\">hrine, Basic</span></h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle1\">Just because one finds themselves in the grip of the void does not mean that one must be separate of their gods. Some say they are never closer then without a world to come between them and the mighty forces they may pay heed to. Basic shrines are little more than an appropriate altar with matching iconography to a particular deity.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"><br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p>","unidentified":""},"source":"","type":"","modifiers":[],"damage":{"parts":[]},"critical":{"parts":[]},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"sfrpg","systemVersion":"0.22.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672510147667,"modifiedTime":1673333903583,"lastModifiedBy":"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY"},"_id":"CHVUKThUCecehBum","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY":3}}
{"name":"Shrine, Opulent","type":"starshipExpansionBay","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"cost":5,"costMultipliedBySize":false,"pcu":10,"isPowered":true,"description":{"chat":"","gmnotes":"","short":"","value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Name PCU Cost (In BP)<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Hive 2 2<br>Rift 10 3<br>Shrine, Basic 1 1<br>Shrine, Advanced 3 2<br>Shrine, Opulent 10 5</span></p><h3><span class=\"fontstyle0\">S</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-size:9pt;\">hrine, Opulent</span></h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An opulent shrine must be devoted to a specific god or gods that form a cohesive team (A shrine to the Sun Queen and Blaze, for example). Such a shrine is made to feel like one has stepped into the eternal realm of their divine host, with illusionary imitations of the divine or profane servants present to guide the faithful through rituals to please the gods. Holy or unholy water is available, up to three portions worth a day, constantly recycled from the ship’s water as needed. Divine rituals enjoy a +2 circumstance bonus within such a place.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p>","unidentified":""},"source":"","type":"","modifiers":[],"damage":{"parts":[]},"critical":{"parts":[]},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"sfrpg","systemVersion":"0.22.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672510147667,"modifiedTime":1673333903583,"lastModifiedBy":"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY"},"_id":"my0lNQjZj91MNrmY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7Idr7n4PmaIACOqY":3}}
